t><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=637.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.purgatory.net/alex/medion.jpg width=64 height=64></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: NO respect cause of lvl</span><hr size=1> With that big of a level difference, I wouldn't be surprised at all if that paladin was a better tank than you, both at taking damage and holding aggro. <p><html><body><p style="font-size:110%"><b><a href="http://www.suckbird.com/roster/profile.asp?who=Iskandar" STYLE="text-decoration: none"  target="_blank">Veteran Iskandar Alazeem</a><br><a href=http://www.steelwarrior.org STYLE="text-decoration: none" target="_blank">Steel Warrior</a> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior STYLE="text-decoration: none"  target="_blank">moderator</a><br><a href=http://www.keepersofthefaith.org STYLE="text-decoration: none"  target="_blank">Keepers of the Faith</a></b></p></body></html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uglatius2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/8/02 9:57:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=637.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   RE: No respect</span><hr size=1> Unfortunately level &gt; AC &amp; HP.  Particularly when you are talking more than a level or two.  If that wasn't the case the standard advice would be to get AA points before level 60 because being in the mid 50s makes you as effective as a 60, if you have the right gear.  But that isn't the case.<br><br>Also it sounds like a small case of Main Tank envy.  Its very easy and completely normal for players who don't get to Main Tank on a regular basis to have some resentment towards those that do.  Being a good Main Tank however, requires more than just level and good gear.  And not every player is up to it.<br><br>If you are, as you level and continue to raid with your guild, it will become evident.  And unless your guild has a real surplus of warriors, you will get your chance to show your stuff.  Be patient.  Pick up every tip you possibly can.  And understand that every dog has his day, be ready to grab the opportunity when it comes and run with it.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usmushums.showPublicProfile?language=EN>smushums</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 823<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/8/02 10:20:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=637.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: RE: No respect</span><hr size=1> think of it this way..<br>if your not the main tank your not the first to die! <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7023  target="web">smushums<a</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utugurok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tugurok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/8/02 1:31:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=637.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pantheon.yale.edu/~bdiebold/images/TugReal.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: RE: No respect</span><hr size=1> Need to check the gear on that paladin, but yes, definitely, the paladin should have been tanking. 6 levels &gt; whatever (probably small) margin of AC and hps you had. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uturomtoesmasher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Turom Toesmasher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 228<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/8/02 1:36:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=637.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.gaiahealing.com/everquest/turom_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: RE: No respect</span><hr size=1> Reavers can summon, you are 49, therefore you cannot taunt them.<br><br>The Paladin was the right choice for MT.<br><br>To be perfectly honest, I think a lot of Ogre Warriors have a god complex.  Yeah, you have good stamina and can't be stunned from the front, but you are not the *only* tank choice out there. <p><Table Style='Filter: Alpha(Opacity=100, FinishOpacity=50, Style=3, StartX=85, FinishX=20, StartY=0, FinishY=0)'><B><Font Color=White Face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11741" target="magelo"><Font Color=White>Turom Toesmasher</Font></a><br>Warlord<br>The Seventh Hammer<br></Font></B></Table></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uturomtoesmasher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Turom Toesmasher</A> at: 4/8/02 1:39:11 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udracillionofqeynos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DracillionofQeynos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/8/02 2:26:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=637.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: RE: No respect</span><hr size=1> I think most warriors have gone through this at some point.  It just takes an understanding of why level is so critical and why you shouldn't be MT.  When I was in my mid 50s and my gear was utter junk, I got told by some that I couldn't tank certain mobs.  At the time, it made me a bit mad.  (pride...dumb pride)  But now, I totally understand where that person was coming from and they were right.  <br><br>So when your told you can't or aren't going to be the MT, just try to see it from the raid leader's perspective and understand why.  In this instance, 55 Pal vs a 49 War, it was the right call.  <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=127089">Dracillion of Qeynos</a><BR>Warlord of Omani<BR>Bertoxxulous Server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uazlanaicelander.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azlana Icelander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sexies Warlady in all o'Norrath</BR>     ...an da moon too!</BR>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 261<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/8/02 3:49:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=637.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.bellatlantic.net/~suzkim/Azsig4.jpeg width=116 height=165></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: RE: No respect</span><hr size=1> Level an AC does play big part on MT stuff. Buh ya time will come. <br><br>Likes mes neva got ta MT on any big mobs... not till one nigh we up in hate an is first time we was gonna attempt da *new* Inny. Guess wot! M'da oldes warrior dere. Anywho when mes guild leader say ta me 'ya ready ta tank a God?' M'say sure! Oh boy... well makes long story short wes won! <br><br>Afta dat m'gots ta do more MT stuff. Tooks till m'was likes 59 ta be able ta do it buh now does more often. <br><br>So keeps dat fat ogre chin up an keep on a goin. <p><HR><center><table border="0" height="41" width=50%><tr><td colspan="3" height="17"><p align="center"><img border="0" src=http://members.bellatlantic.net/~suzkim/Azlana5.gif width="220" height="59"></td></tr><tr><td align="left" height="10"><font color="#FFCC00" face="Copperplate Gothic Light" size="2">Warlady</font></td><td align="center" height="10"><a href="http://www.ringofshadows.org"><font color="#FFCC00" face="Copperplate Gothic Light" size="2" nowrap>Ring of Shadows</font></a></td><td align="right" height="10"><font color="#FFCC00" face="Copperplate Gothic Light" size="2">Veeshan</font></td></tr></table></center><HR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utalicmoore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talic Moore</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://forums.interealms.com/ranger/images/icons/Yin_Yang.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Hero of the Realms</BR>Guardian of the Keep</BR>STEEL WARRIOR Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 845<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/8/02 3:55:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=637.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eyesonff.com/ff1/fighter.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: RE: No respect</span><hr size=1> It's almost definite that the paladin would have been a better main tank, six levels can make a big difference.<br><br>However, this sort of thing is not confined to Everquest, or just this situation. It's everyone, in game and out. Xexys and I have discussed more than once similar situations that I have been forced to go through... for a different reason, but the same general thing. <p><img src=http://www.warghoul.com/images/talicsig.jpg ></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uroshinbertson.showPublicProfile?language=EN>roshinbertson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/8/02 4:55:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=637.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  maybe i'm not understanding???</span><hr size=1> if my ac and hp was better then his...wouldn't i make the better meat shield?  It was a CoM raid reavers...i'm not really mad or envious or anything...i was just wondering...i guess the way i wrote it made me sound upset...<br><br>So from the begining...why wouldn't me(49 war) with better stats then a 55 paly be a better tank?...just curious...to help me understand that...<br><br>i know i can't tank gods and uber mobs...but i didn't think the reavers are anything...and i tanked the named ghost up there most of the fight when we only had a shaman to heal...cleric gated out he had to leave...<br><br>thanks for replies....<br><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=108737" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.pitt.edu/~gjpst18/RoshSig.jpg" border="0"></a>  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uemiliaeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EmiliaEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/8/02 5:06:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=637.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: maybe i'm not understanding???</span><hr size=1> Tanking = Keeping the mob on you AND beeing mana efficient<br><br>You were a bit more mana sufficient.<br>Paladins was MUCH better at keeping agro.<br><br>Its not only ac/hp thing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Even in ToV / NToV you will see paladins/sk tank <br>(add tank of course)<br><br>Yes they are less efficient tanks, but they can gain<br>and keep agro EASY. While for a warrior this takes time.<br><br>Take the best warrior in EQ, give him the BEST weapons<br>in the game (BoC/HG) have him reach 1600ac 5500hp.<br><br>Want to bet a 60 paladin/sk will make a better add tank ?<br><br>I didnt say more efficient i said better.<br><br>Atm i am sorry to say but the paladin despite the lower ac/hp<br>was surely better at getting &amp; keeping agro.<br>So it was a good choice to get him to MT.<br><br>Get 58, get Frosty &amp; Ven axe .....<br>Now ask if they will ask a pal 58 or you to MT ....... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>  <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5132"/A></BR>     Warlord of Rallos Zek</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcol