m)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=637.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tpsabre/images/fasnew.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: NO respect cause of lvl</span><hr size=1> It wasn't a matter of no respect towards you or any other person there that was not asked to tank.  It was a matter of where the group/raid was and who was there.<br><br>Someone else here brought up a very good point.  Your skills have been capped for quite a number of levels.  They won't unlock until you level out of 50th into 51st.  <br><br>Some folks do tend to take it personally when they are &quot;replaced&quot; by another to Main Tank.  It all comes down to, as a whole, what combinations do we have at this raid to provide the best chance of survival.<br><br>Here's an aside.  Past couple nights I've been in Sebilis with some really great folks.  Our Monk was the puller and the Main Tank.  He was not only awesome but is a really cool guy.  The difference between us, level wise, is 1 but skills, gear, class abilities all came into play.  He could avoid blows like the devil vs. me, metal man  lol, absorbing the blows.  Let alone taunt... lets not go there ... haha I gave up trying to taunt unless we had a problem happen and we needed to multi tank.<br><br><br>Cheers<br><br>Faseti<br>59th Myrmidon<br>LoH - 7th Hammer<br> <p><P><CENTER><IMG src = "http://members.aol.com/tpsabre/images//fassig59.jpg"></CENTER></P></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=thelix>Thelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/10/02 7:18:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=637.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.animation-station.com/cartoon/images/cart0037.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: NO respect cause of lvl</span><hr size=1> Basically what they are trying to say is with your defensive skills at 49 are &lt; a 55 pally basically because a reaver would rip through you like so.<br><br>A reaver_001 hits you for 130 points of damage.<br>A reaver_001 hits you for 121 points of damage.<br>A reaver_001 kicks you for 35 points of damage.<br>etc....etc....etc....<br><br>where as a paladin 6 levels higher then you would be more likely to see something like this.<br><br>A reaver_001 hits pally_055 for 110 points of damage.<br>A reaver_001 hits pally_055 for 89 points of damage.<br>A reaver_001 kicks pally_055 for 15 points of damage.<br><br>Level plays a HUGE factor on how often a mob hits you for around their max damage. I have experienced this SOOO many times in Exp and raiding situations. I have been in groups where a pally/SK has been in the group with me and has been 2 - 3 levels higher then me and takes less damage because they are getting hit for less even though I have higher AC and more Hp's. <br><br>I know it can be hard to grow up all your levels KNOWING that a warrior *should* always tank, but the higher you go you'll see that it's more about situational tanking rather then sticking to the myth that a warrior *should* ALWAYS tank.<br><br>Only realy advice I can give you is trust that the raid leader/guild knows what they are doing when they ask a hybrid to tank rather then a warrior.<br><br>I know it is hard to get used to but the more you keep an open mind and experience the benifit of using non warriors to tank in certain situations(even on seemingly trival mobs) the better off you'll be.<br><br>Stick with it, grind out some exp, kick some butt <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12614>Thelix Thunderblaze</a><BR>Level 58 warrior<BR>~~E'CI~~<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=danoorngnollbane>Danoorn Gnollbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/10/02 11:13:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=637.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: NO respect cause of lvl</span><hr size=1> Brother,<br>I feel your pain. I had some of those same questions and looked at the role of the Warrior as &quot;TANK&quot;.<br><br>Then my guild was kind enough to let me tank after I ranted a bit. I tanked a mob that:<br><br>1) Was yellow to me at 53. (broken Taunt button).<br>2) That required slow to land. (Dead Shammy - See 1)<br>3) That hit me VERY hard. (OOM cleric)<br>4) Because of the above 3 mob ping-pongs off the casters.<br><br>WIPE OUT!<br><br>After a hard lesson learned, I went on an experience binge and made 60 as quick as I could. I passed on raids, even the ones that benefited me.<br><br>Shortly thereafter I was asked to MT just about everything, with another Warlord in our guild. Now I get tells asking me to MT on raids and not only from my guildmates.<br><br>All in all, it's about what you want to do. The best MT has levels, gear, and experience in being MT. But I might suggest that if you want to MT, get the levels first. As you get levels, watch closely what the MT's around you are doing. Ask questions. Gear seems to fall from the sky after that.<br><br>If you aren't interested in being MT right away, COOL, camp whatever you like and have fun doing it. Still ask the questions, as you will be asked someday.<br><br>IMHO, if the MT and SA fall, it's very hard for the rest of the raid to recover and often times it's a wipeout. After Levels, experience and know-how is key. Gear just kinda comes.<br><br>Good luck!<br><br>Dano <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uestebar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Estebar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/10/02 6:34:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=637.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: NO respect cause of lvl</span><hr size=1> More of the same.<br><br>This past weekend I had the chance to main tank in Umbral Plains (raid winding down), but I managed to convince the leader that I would be a bad choice.<br><br>At 53, everything was equal or higher level than I was, and weapon aggro seemed real low there.  Used a 56 sk as MA instead.  The extra spell aggro was enough to pretty much get rid of any ping-ponging.  Aggro control may have been better than earlier when we had a 60 warrior + enc hate spells(took a lot more healing though).<br><br><br>Last time in CoM was fun, until 6 reavers popped in a row and I went LD in the middle of number 6.  Having taunt is reassuring when you're blind and not sure if you're actually hitting.  Also having a sound card so you can tell that you still have aggro.<br><br>Never thought of it before, but anyone know if you can actually cast spells while blind? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ufoolsfizzelmore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fools Fizzelmore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/12/02 2:19:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=637.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://freepages.ugo.com/oooglie/files/Ani.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: NO respect cause of lvl</span><hr size=1> As everyone has said above lvl 55 v lvl49 is a MASSIVE difference.<br><br>Tanking is NOT only about taking damage. it is about holding agro. Just pure melee the pali should be outdamaging you..just pure melee. Add into that that at lvl 49 you can not taunt the mobs.....then also add in the fact that a lvl 55 pali even with slightly less ac/hps will take a LOT less damage than you would.<br><br>All these point to pali tank.<br><br>But do not take it personally...it is a pain you have to carry for a little while. Just wait until you have your first defensive skill....then you will be able to tank more. At 55 you will be a MUCH more effictive tank than a 55 pali (even with the same ac/hps as each other).<br><br>Try to remember Sk's and palis are plate classes and can wear almost the same armour we can. At the end of the day palis/sks have comparitive ac/hps to warrior..but the /defensive and our damage mitigation is greater than thiers.<br><br>Try not to lose heart due to it, just let it help you try to focus on getting your warrior to 51+<br><br>take care <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>cuch. <p><p><centre><B><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=78052 ">Cuchullan</A><br>Warlord<br><A HREF="http://www.insidiousblood.net/">IB</A></b></center></p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">